title: Paul McCartney - 1997-11-24 - New York - Oprah
description: Here is a nice broadcast with a great Macca interview and short performance. Please enjoy, share with friends (for FREE!!!) and please seed :) I use fast servers but also need your help, there's too much downloaders to handle. I really want to share more rare stuff that is not available in shops, but i need your help to keep my collection alive. Please let your PC run for a while!!! Stuff like this needs to be preserved for future generations of music lovers. Thanks to all the peers from everywhere seeding my huge archive, i love you! ================================================================================ Paul McCartney "Oprah" Taped: 11-20-97 Broadcast: 11-24-97 Another video from the Graceful Duck Archive. Cable > Beta HiFi > Edit Beta HiFi > Playback Sony SL-HF900 > Standalone Panasonic DMR-E50 (XP) No Artwork Chapters approximately every 5 minutes NTSC TRT: 41:46 Audio codec: AC3 Audio bitrate: 256 kb/s Video codec: MPEG2 Video bitrate: 9096 kb/s "This just may be the biggest show ever." - These are the first words viewers heard when they tuned in "Oprah" on Monday, November 24th, 1997. This episode, taped in New York City, features a star-struck Oprah Winfrey up close and personal with Paul McCartney. Paul seems happy, candid and humble. Oprah reaches over and touches Paul several times, gushing like a teenager at times. In addition to the full length interview covering a variety of interesting topics, Paul performs "Young Boy" and "Flaming Pie" with a set of video screens behind him playing pre-recorded video of himself on different instruments. In the next segment, Oprah and Paul unveil the world premier of his new video "Beautiful Night".
